@startuml roles_casting
' Diagram 4/5 — roles, casts, evidence: how a seat gets a model (or a human).
' Source of truth: roles.yaml, casts/, src/agora/fleet/cast.py.

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

[roles.yaml\nROLE CONTRACTS\nrequires + harness config] as ROLES
[casts/<envelope>.yaml\nBINDINGS per hardware\nprofile | human, resident,\nevidence | waiver] as CASTS
[profiles.yaml\nmodel identity] as PROF
[capability matrix\nevidence rows keyed\n(model x probe_version x\nharness x tool-surface)] as MATRIX
[local manifest store\nmodel sizes (bytes on disk)] as MANIFEST

[validate_cast] as VAL
[load_cast -> seat table] as LOAD
[Orchestrator seats\nimplementer / tester /\nverifier / planner / ...] as SEATS

ROLES --> VAL
CASTS --> VAL
PROF --> VAL
MATRIX ..> VAL : evidence lookup
MANIFEST ..> VAL : resident VRAM sum
VAL --> LOAD
LOAD --> SEATS

note bottom of VAL
  four rules, all loud:
  1. every profile reference resolves
  2. sum(resident sizes) <= vram_budget
     (sizes from disk, never hand-entered)
  3. evidence at compatible keys OR an
     explicit waiver — **F12**: the tool
     surface a seat exposes is part of
     the evidence key
  4. binding: human is always valid
     (planner precedent; no pretending)
end note

note bottom of CASTS
  one cast file per hardware envelope;
  changing GPUs = choosing a different
  cast, roles.yaml untouched
end note

note bottom of SEATS
  seat manifests are then shaped at
  runtime: allowlist filter + overwrite
  guard under the zero-mutation-
  affordance invariant (**F13**),
  every delta logged
end note
@enduml
